<refentry xml:id="function.yaz-cql-parse" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
 <refnamediv>
  <refname>yaz_cql_parse</refname>
  <refpurpose>Convert CQL to RPN</refpurpose>
 </refnamediv>
 <refsect1 role="description">
  &reftitle.description;
  <methodsynopsis>
   <type>bool</type><methodname>yaz_cql_parse</methodname>
   <methodparam><type>resource</type><parameter>id</parameter></methodparam>
   <methodparam><type>string</type><parameter>cql</parameter></methodparam>
   <methodparam><type>array</type><parameter role="reference">result</parameter></methodparam>
   <methodparam><type>bool</type><parameter>rev</parameter></methodparam>
  </methodsynopsis>
  <simpara>
   This function converts a CQL query to an RPN query which may be passed to
   the <function>yaz_search</function> function to perform a search. It is the
   CQL counterpart of <function>yaz_ccl_parse</function>.
  </simpara>
  <simpara>
   To configure the CQL parser call <function>yaz_cql_conf</function> prior to
   this function.
  </simpara>
 </refsect1>
 <refsect1 role="parameters">
  &reftitle.parameters;
  <para>
   <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
     <term><parameter>id</parameter></term>
     <listitem>
      <simpara>
       The connection resource returned by <function>yaz_connect</function>.
      </simpara>
     </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
     <term><parameter>cql</parameter></term>
     <listitem>
      <simpara>
       The CQL query.
      </simpara>
     </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
     <term><parameter>result</parameter></term>
     <listitem>
      <simpara>
       Holds the result of the conversion. On success, when
       <parameter>rev</parameter> is &false;, the resulting RPN query is stored
       under the key <literal>rpn</literal>; when <parameter>rev</parameter> is
       &true;, the resulting CQL query is stored under the key
       <literal>cql</literal>.
      </simpara>
      <simpara>
       Upon failure, the key <literal>errorcode</literal> holds the error code
       and, where available, <literal>addinfo</literal> holds additional
       information about the failure.
      </simpara>
     </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
     <term><parameter>rev</parameter></term>
     <listitem>
      <simpara>
       When &false;, the CQL query given in <parameter>cql</parameter> is
       converted to RPN. When &true;, the conversion is reversed and the query
       is treated as an RPN query that is converted to CQL.
      </simpara>
     </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
  </para>
 </refsect1>
 <refsect1 role="returnvalues">
  &reftitle.returnvalues;
  <simpara>
   &return.success;
  </simpara>
 </refsect1>
 <refsect1 role="notes">
  &reftitle.notes;
  <note>
   <simpara>
    This function is only available when the extension is built against YAZ
    5.1.0 or later.
   </simpara>
  </note>
 </refsect1>
 <refsect1 role="seealso">
  &reftitle.seealso;
  <simplelist>
   <member><function>yaz_cql_conf</function></member>
   <member><function>yaz_ccl_parse</function></member>
   <member><function>yaz_search</function></member>
  </simplelist>
 </refsect1>
</refentry>
